  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Business Development Manager",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Build and maintain strong relationships with existing clients, ensuring consistent service quality and satisfaction.</li>\n  <li>Identify, pursue, and secure new clients across the private and public sectors, including government agencies.</li>\n  <li>Understand client project requirements and propose suitable manpower solutions — from software developers to PMs and BAs.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with internal teams to expand accounts through upselling and cross-selling IT manpower or project-based services.</li>\n  <li>Support the implementation of business development strategies to achieve monthly and quarterly revenue goals.</li>\n  <li>Monitor market trends, competitor activities, and industry demands to identify growth opportunities.</li>\n  <li>Prepare quotations, proposals, and presentations; manage contract discussions with clients.</li>\n  <li>Maintain accurate client and sales data in CRM systems and report progress to management.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Qualifications</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor’s degree in Business Administration, Marketing, Information Technology, or any related field.</li>\n  <li>At least 3–5 years of experience in business development or account management within the IT outsourcing, staffing, or consulting industry.</li>\n  <li>Strong understanding of IT manpower outsourcing, including software development, project management, and business analysis roles.</li>\n  <li>Proven experience handling both commercial and public sector.</li>\n  <li>Excellent communication, presentation, and negotiation skills.</li>\n  <li>Results-driven, resourceful, and able to work independently in a fast-paced environment.</li>\n</ul>",
